OL,6,FWealthier Scots are facing a double tax
OL,7,Fblow next year after the Scottish
OL,8,FGovernment announced plans to increase
OL,9,Fboth income and council tax from April.
OL,11,FAnyone earning more than #43,662 will
OL,12,Fface a higher tax bill due to changes
OL,13,Fto the higher and top rates, which will
OL,14,Fincrease from 41p to 42p and from 46p
OL,15,Fto 47p respectively.
OL,17,FThe threshold at which the top rate of
OL,18,Ftax kicks in will also be lowered from
OL,19,F#150,000 to #125,140, in line with a
OL,20,Fsimilar change being made in other
OL,21,Fparts of the UK.
OL,3,CWealthy Scots asked to pay more as
OL,4,Cincome tax and council tax to rise
